File: Naspers’ newly listed pay-television business Multichoice Group notified workers of its intention to retrench 1,790 workers. JOHANNESBURG  - A South African trade union said on Friday that Naspers’ newly listed pay-television business Multichoice Group had notified workers of its intention to retrench 1,790 workers. READ: MultiChoice could retrench more than 2000 staff The employees were notified on Friday afternoon but the union has not been officially informed, “which makes the process unlawful”, the Information Communication and Technology Union (ICTU) said in a statement.